      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH). Both are directly linked to the clinical decision criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time distributions) support mechanistic interpretation. QoI traceability matrix maps each QoI to the decision criterion.",
