    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Discretization error achieves Gradation 3 (required: 2), providing additional confidence margin. Output comparison demonstrates mean NIH error of 4.2% against experimental benchmark, well within the 10% acceptance criterion. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented rationale in assessment plan AP-2025-CPB-001. Provenance chain is complete: validation results link to experimental datasets, uncertainty quantification activities, and foundational literature (FDA pump round-robin). The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the defined COU. Decision accepted without offset rationale as no factor shortfall exists.",
